Privacy Policy

Effective Date: 02.07.2023

This Privacy Policy describes how Memorati ("we," "us," or "our") collects, uses, and protects the information you provide when using our mobile application ("App").

1. Information We Collect
We may collect the following types of information when you use our App:

1.1 Non-Personal Information:
- Device Information: We may collect non-personal information about the device you use to access the App, such as device type, operating system, and unique device identifiers.

2. How We Use Your Information
We may use the collected information for the following purposes:

2.1 Personalization: To personalize your experience and provide customized content and recommendations based on your preferences.
2.2 Analytics: To analyze usage patterns, improve the App's functionality, and optimize user experience.

3. Information Sharing
We do not sell, trade, or otherwise transfer your information to third parties without your consent. However, we may share your information in the following circumstances:

3.1 Service Providers: We may engage trusted third-party service providers to assist us in operating the App and delivering the requested services. These service providers are obligated to maintain the confidentiality and security of your information.
3.2 Legal Obligations: We may disclose your information if required by law or in response to valid legal requests, such as court orders or government regulations.
3.3 Protection of Rights: We may disclose your information to protect our rights, enforce our policies, respond to claims of infringement, or protect the safety and security of users and the public.

4. Data Security
We take reasonable measures to protect your information from unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction. However, please note that no method of data transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure.

5. Children's Privacy
Our App is not intended for use by children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If you believe we have collected personal information from a child, please contact us immediately.

6. Changes to this Privacy Policy
We reserve the right to modify or update this Privacy Policy at any time. We encourage you to review this policy periodically for any changes. Your continued use of the App after the posting of changes constitutes your acceptance of such changes.

7. Contact Us
If you have any questions, concerns, or feedback regarding this Privacy Policy or our privacy practices, please contact us at https://forms.gle/Cqatu1FVoLVZhwqN6.

By using the App, you signify your acceptance of this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree with this policy, please do not use the App.

